{
  "page": "Tytos Lannister's first mistress",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Tytos Lannister's first mistress</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Tytos Lannister's first mistress</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">lowborn</a> woman who served as a <a href=\"/index.php/Wet_nurse\" title=\"Wet nurse\">wet nurse</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Her name is unknown. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tytos_Lannister%27s_first_mistress&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Marbrand\" title=\"Jeyne Marbrand\">Jeyne Marbrand</a> died not long after giving birth to <a href=\"/index.php/Gerion_Lannister\" title=\"Gerion Lannister\">Gerion Lannister</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_255_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">255&#160;AC</a>. During the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Ninepenny_Kings\" title=\"War of the Ninepenny Kings\">War of the Ninepenny Kings</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/260_AC\" title=\"260 AC\">260&#160;AC</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a> remained at <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> with his mistress, Gerion's young wet nurse. Tytos often retreated to her comforts rather than deal with ruling the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>. By <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_267_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">267&#160;AC</a>, the wet nurse had been replaced by <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister%27s_second_mistress\" title=\"Tytos Lannister&#39;s second mistress\">Tytos's second mistress</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tytos_Lannister%27s_first_mistress&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Westerlands: House Lannister Under the Dragons.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403233050\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.075 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.282 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 497/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10453/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 4139/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 784/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1178/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.190/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.43 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  275.984      1 -total\n 94.16%  259.875      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 93.49%  258.021      1 Template:Infobox\n 12.73%   35.141     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.28%   11.820      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  2.96%    8.160      3 Template:Date\n  2.16%    5.959      2 Template:Ref\n  1.31%    3.617      2 Template:Ref/core\n  0.58%    1.608      1 Template:References\n  0.32%    0.893      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:23541-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403233050 and revisi